elements. It is the annotations-only module used by Swagger Core and compatible tooling to derive OpenAPI definitions from Java code.\",\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/3.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-named-locks/1.9.25/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-connector-basic/2.0.8/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jakarta RESTful Web Services API defines the annotations, interfaces, and core types used to build RESTful web services on the JVM. This artifact provides the API contracts for resources, requests, responses, media types, filters, and client/server extension points rather than a concrete implementation.\",\nmetadata/jakarta.ws.rs/jakarta.ws.rs-api/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Jakarta RESTful Web Services API defines the standard annotations, interfaces, and runtime contracts for building RESTful services and clients in Jakarta EE. This artifact provides only the API types for resources, request and response handling, media negotiation, filters, interceptors, and extension points while implementations are supplied by Jakarta REST runtimes.\",\nmetadata/org.xmlunit/xmlunit-placeholders/2.10.2/reachability-metadata.json:28:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-classloader-commons/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Quarkus Classloader Commons provides small shared utilities for Quarkus bootstrap class loading. It converts between Java class names and .class resource names and identifies JDK-internal package names used by class loader logic.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-named-locks/2.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-connector-basic/1.9.25/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-named-locks/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Maven Resolver Named Locks provides synchronization primitives for named lock coordination within Maven Artifact Resolver. It includes local, file-based, and no-op named lock factories used to guard concurrent access to shared resolver resources.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-named-locks/index.json:39:    \"description\" : \"Maven Resolver Named Locks provides synchronization primitives for named lock coordination within Maven Artifact Resolver. It includes local, file-based, and no-op named lock factories used to guard concurrent access to shared resolver resources.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.resolver/maven-resolver-connector-basic/2.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/org.clojure/google-closure-library-third-party/0.0-20150505-021ed5b3/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-junit-common/3.33.1/reachability-metadata.json:32:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/org.glassfish/javax.servlet/3.1/reachability-metadata.json:16:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/org.clojure/google-closure-library-third-party/0.0-20250515-f04e4c0e/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/net.sf.kxml/kxml2/2.3.0/reachability-metadata.json:28:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/org.glassfish/javax.annotation/index.json:15:    \"description\" : \"This artifact provides the JSR-250 Common Annotations API as an OSGi bundle for GlassFish. It defines standard javax.annotation lifecycle, resource-injection, security, generated-code, and SQL data-source annotations used by Java EE components.\"\nmetadata/org.glassfish/javax.annotation/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"This artifact provides the JSR-250 Common Annotations API as an OSGi bundle for GlassFish. It defines standard javax.annotation lifecycle, resource-injection, security, generated-code, and SQL data-source annotations used by Java EE components.\",\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-bootstrap-app-model/3.34.0/reachability-metadata.json:186:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/io.grpc/grpc-netty-shaded/1.68.0/reachability-metadata.json:271:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-bootstrap-app-model/3.33.1/reachability-metadata.json:186:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/io.grpc/grpc-alts/1.68.0/reachability-metadata.json:1029:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/io.grpc/grpc-alts/1.68.0/reachability-metadata.json:1065:      \"glob\" : \"sun/util/logging/resources/logging_en.properties\"\nmetadata/io.grpc/grpc-alts/1.68.0/reachability-metadata.json:1072:      \"glob\" : \"sun/util/logging/resources/logging_en_US.properties\"\nmetadata/io.grpc/grpc-alts/1.68.0/reachability-metadata.json:1075:      \"bundle\" : \"sun.util.logging.resources.logging\"\nmetadata/javax.annotation/jsr250-api/index.json:10:    \"description\": \"Provides the JSR-250 Common Annotations API for the Java platform, including lifecycle, resource injection, and security annotations. It defines annotations such as @Resource, @PostConstruct, @PreDestroy, and role-based security markers for use by compliant runtimes and applications.\",\nmetadata/org.jboss/jandex/2.4.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json:11:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/org.glassfish/javax.transaction/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"The GlassFish javax.transaction artifact provides the Java Transaction API types for coordinating transactions between applications, application servers, transaction managers, and resource managers. It defines standard interfaces and exceptions for transaction demarcation, synchronization callbacks, and XA resource enlistment without providing a transaction manager implementation.\",\nmetadata/jakarta.xml.bind/jakarta.xml.bind-api/3.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:2:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/org.postgresql/postgresql/42.7.3/reachability-metadata.json:1368:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/com.clickhouse/clickhouse-client/0.9.0/reachability-metadata.json:16:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/com.clickhouse/clickhouse-data/0.9.0/reachability-metadata.json:178:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/com.clickhouse/org.apache.commons.compress/1.9.2/reachability-metadata.json:184:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/jakarta.xml.bind/jakarta.xml.bind-api/4.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:21:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/javax.annotation/javax.annotation-api/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Provides the JSR-250 Common Annotations API for Java, including lifecycle, resource, security, and SQL data source annotations. It defines standard annotation types used by frameworks and containers without providing their runtime implementations.\",\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-bootstrap-runner/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Quarkus Bootstrap Runner provides production runtime bootstrap classes, entry points, class loaders, resource access, and logging setup for Quarkus applications packaged with the runner architecture. It is used by generated Quarkus applications to load application classes and resources at runtime while keeping the bootstrap layer minimal and parent-first dependency behavior controlled.\",\nmetadata/xalan/xalan/2.7.0/reachability-metadata.json:975:      \"type\": \"sun.text.resources.CollationData\"\nmetadata/xalan/xalan/2.7.0/reachability-metadata.json:978:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/javax.servlet/servlet-api/2.4.public_draft/reachability-metadata.json:22:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/org.jboss.arquillian.test/arquillian-test-spi/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Arquillian Test SPI defines the service provider interfaces, events, contexts, and extension contracts used by Arquillian test runners and enrichers. It lets integrations plug into Arquillian Core's test lifecycle, resource injection, execution decisions, and test result handling.\",\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-fs-util/1.3.0/reachability-metadata.json:10:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/javax.servlet/servlet-api/2.3/reachability-metadata.json:22:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/org.jboss.arquillian.test/arquillian-test-api/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Arquillian Test API provides the public annotation used by Arquillian tests to request runtime-managed test resources. It is a small Java API module that integrates Arquillian test code with the Arquillian Core resource injection model.\",\nmetadata/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.0.6/reachability-metadata.json:30:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/javax.servlet/servlet-api/2.4/reachability-metadata.json:22:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/org.apache.santuario/xmlsec/4.0.4/reachability-metadata.json:268:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/org.apache.santuario/xmlsec/4.0.4/reachability-metadata.json:294:      \"bundle\": \"org/apache/xml/security/resource/xmlsecurity\"\nmetadata/org.mariadb.jdbc/mariadb-java-client/3.5.2/reachability-metadata.json:31:  \"resources\": [\nmetadata/javax.servlet/javax.servlet-api/3.1.0/reachability-metadata.json:16:  \"resources\" : [\nmetadata/org.mariadb/r2dbc-mariadb/1.1.3/reachability-metadata.json:10:  \"resources\": [\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
